  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rwanda - Strong Winds</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 1st April 2017 at 3:00 pm, Gatsibo district located in the Eastern Province of Rwanda experienced heavy rainfall
associated with heavy storms which, resulted in destruction of houses and community farm lands in Kiramuruzi Sector
Nyabisindu Cell. The affected area is located 36 kilometers from Gatsibo District, 40 kilometers from the Eastern
Province office and 70 kilometers from the City of Kigali.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The storm and heavy wind-affected population&#x2019;s immediate needs are met through the provision of essential emergency
relief, shelter items, hygiene promotion assistance, targeting a total number of 675 people (135 households) whose
items/properties were destroyed in Kiramuruzi Sector, Gatsibo districts, Eastern Province, Rwanda.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is located in Kiramuruzi Sector, Gatsibo districts, Eastern Province, Rwanda.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides emergency relief in the form of non food items, hygiene promotion, and shelter.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project reaches 675 people (135 households).</narrative>
  </description>
